500|$|John of Küküllő {{emphasized}} that Louis [...] "ruled neither with passion, nor with <b>arbitrariness,</b> {{but rather as}} the guardian of righteousness". Antonio Bonfini also described Louis as a just king wandering among his subjects in disguise to protect them the royal officials' arbitrary acts. Even Jan of Czarnków underlined that Louis [...] "did not rule in an absolute manner; on the contrary, the foundations ... of [...] freedom were laid by him".|$|E
